The Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) has emerged from the constitutional controversy that the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies have formulated against the presidential decree that advances the so-called "analogue cutup" from 2021 to 2015, because the eight votes required to invalidate it have not been gathered.
