The draft award, prepared by Minister Olga Sánchez Cordero, proposed the decree's declaration as a non-constitutional, because radio and television regulations are a statutory assignment to the Federal Telecommunications Commission (Cofetel), in contravention of the principles of hierarchical subordination and statutory reservation.
Only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero voted in favour of the project.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies have promoted two constitutional controversies to challenge the decree and to admit the complaints, Minister Sánchez Cordero suspended the application of the decree and all the actions envisaged by it for the digital transition.
