It will be recalled that Michoacán has not approved either its Constitution or its Electoral Code of State or its Electoral Justice Act, at the same time that the Congress of the State has approved the reforms shortly before the legal deadline for this electoral process to enter into force and the Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel has omitted his publication within the time limit provided for by the Law of the Official Journal of the State, with the argument that he had some objections.
On the same November 9, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the Local Legislative Power and qualified as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the state representative for constitutional reforms, as he does not have the right to "sanction or challenge them".
Interviewed on the possibility of "voting by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that with the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the IEM General Council, it will be possible to make the partial and total discounts of votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial count of votes, one or more electoral packages, may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no poll record and count in the ballot file is not in the chairman's case; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of votes received in all polls of the election may be made when there is an index of the fact that the difference between the alleged candidate who wins the respective election and the one who obtained the second place in the poll is equal or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition by the representative of the party and/or coalition who presented the second one of the candidates reported.
The total voter count may also be made if at the end of the joint count it follows that the difference between the alleged winner and that of the second place is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is the express petition of the representative of the political party whose candidate has gone out second, in which case the electoral packages that were subject to the partial count will be excluded.
It should be noted that this is the situation of Morelia's election, where according to the PRSP, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without accounting for the 129 votes of the 923 total minutes.
